Koscielny on why he left #Arsenal: &quot;A Premier League season is very long. It requires a lot physically &amp; mentally. I didn't feel I could play 40-50 matches &amp; I didn't want to end my career with injuries. I've gone down a level, but to take more pleasure&quot;<br />
<br />
Koscielny: &quot;With my family, we felt it was time. Everything was in my thinking: football, my physical state, my wife, my children, the daily life we could have. I can only say I left with my head held high. All of those I worked with for 9 years... everyone respected my decision&quot;

Emery on Aubameyang: &quot;Now he is more confident &amp; mature in the Premier League compared to when I arrived last year. He scored a lot of goals last year but has now also taken a big responsibility within the team. He is one of the captains who can manage the dressing room&quot;<br />
<br />
Emery on Aubameyang: &quot;I will speak with him in my office, the hotel or the dressing room. First we built a human connection &amp; then as a player &amp; then I know I can ask him what I want &amp; what the team needs &ndash; he always listens &amp; will always give his best to provide that&quot;
